ase%20a%20larger%20house%20that%20we%20could%20reside%20in%20as%20well%20as%20rent%2C%20both%20long-term%20and%20on%20AirBnB.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20outside%20entrance%20into%20the%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20with%20a%20bright%20red%20door.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b043889751e300192a0181%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20big%20red%20door%20is%20entry%20into%20the%20two-bedroom%20apartment%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Qaid%20Jivan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20spending%20nearly%20two%20years%20s%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvancouver-realtor-sold-120-million-real-estate-last-year-2022-8%5C%22%3Eearching%20around%20Vancouver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20100-year-old%20house%20that%20no%20one%20seemed%20to%20want.%20The%20house%20was%20in%20rough%20shape%20and%20had%20a%20weird%20layout%20for%20most%20people%20because%20it%20had%20nine%20bedrooms%2C%20three%20kitchens%2C%20five%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20multiple%20entrances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20though%2C%20we%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20revenue-generating%20opportunity%20before%20we%20have%20kids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Qaid%20Jivan%20and%20Alyssa%20McDonald%20posing%20in%20the%2070s-themed%20orange%20bedroom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b034349751e3001929fe14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMcdonald%20and%20Jivan%20in%20one%20of%20the%2070s-inspired%20bedrooms.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Qaid%20Jivan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20paid%20%241.45%20million%20for%20the%20house%20and%20estimated%20that%20we'd%20spend%20around%20%24150%2C000%20on%20renovations.%20But%20we%20challenged%20ourselves%20to%20spend%20under%20%245%2C000%20to%20turn%20the%20space%20we%20planned%20to%20use%20for%20our%20AirBnB%C2%A0%20into%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment.%20Here's%20exactly%20what%20we%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20did%20most%20of%20the%20work%20ourselves%20and%20only%20did%20what%20was%20necessary%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-renovation-cost-each-room-2019-6%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20renovate%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20AirBnB%20space%20mostly%20on%20our%20own%20and%20with%20friends%20to%20save%20labor%20costs.%20We%20did%20hire%20a%20contractor%20to%20fix%20up%20the%20bathroom%20and%20paid%20around%20%242%2C700%20for%20a%20new%20toilet%2C%20shower%20kit%2C%20and%20fixtures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20we%20saved%20money%20was%20by%20not%20installing%20a%20full%20kitchen%20in%20the%20space.%20Having%20to%20build%20out%20plumbing%20for%20that%20could%20have%20cost%20more%20than%20%245%2C000.%20Instead%2C%20we%20installed%20a%20kitchenette%20which%20cost%20under%20%24200.%20Since%20most%20of%20our%20guests%20stay%20for%20an%20average%20of%202.5%20nights%2C%20we've%20found%20that%20this%20equipment%20is%20enough%20for%20them%20to%20make%20quick%20meals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22763%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20kitchenette.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b046ba9751e300192a0263%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22572%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJivan%20and%20McDonald%20created%20a%20hotel-style%20kitchenette%20for%20the%20space.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Qaid%20Jivan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20followed%20the%20same%20approach%20with%20the%20bathroom.%20Instead%20of%20building%20out%20a%20shower%2C%20we%20purchased%20a%20shower%20kit%2C%20which%20is%20basically%20a%20pre-built%20shower%2C%20this%20cost%20%241%2C000%2C%20a%20third%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20custom%20shower.%20We%20found%20a%20new%20toilet%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ffacebook-marketplace-tips-ways-to-find-the-best-deals-2023-6%5C%22%3Epedestal%20sink%20on%20Facebook%20Marketplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20just%20had%20to%20pay%20the%20plumber%20for%20installation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20found%20good%20deals%20on%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20for%20furniture%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20purchasing%20furniture%20for%20the%20space%2C%20we%20spent%20around%20%241%2C900%20on%20everything%20we%20needed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20keep%20the%20costs%20low%2C%20we%20sourced%20most%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-sell-on-facebook-marketplace%5C%22%3Eitems%20from%20Facebook%20Marketplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20spent%20hours%20every%20day%20refreshing%20the%20platform%20to%20find%20the%20pieces%20I%20wanted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22757%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20workspace%20with%20green%2070s-themed%20desk%20chairs%2C%20a%20white%20desk%2C%20and%20a%20multi-bulb%20floor%20lamp.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b04a649751e300192a0379%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22568%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20workspace%20in%20the%20Airbnb.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Qaid%20Jivan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trick%20to%20securing%20the%20items%20is%20to%20message%20the%20seller%20fast%20and%20be%20direct%20with%20your%20offering.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20best%20deals%20on%20the%20marketplace%20they%20go%20fast%2C%20so%20don't%20bother%20haggling%20or%20you'll%20lose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-decorating-airbnbs-for-five-star-reviews-2022-7%5C%22%3Egive%20the%20space%20a%20unique%20look%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20picked%20a%2070s%20theme%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20done%20in%20conjunction%20with%20our%20close%20friend%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fromy_leah%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERomy%20Sank%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20interior%20designer.%20We%20knew%20we%20wanted%20a%2070s%20theme.%20It's%20an%20era%20me%20and%20Alyssa%20love%2C%20it's%20super%20instagrammable%2C%20and%20it's%20easy%20and%20cheap%20to%20source%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20a%20bunch%20of%20Vancouver%20Sun%20newspapers%20from%201969%2C%20during%20the%20renovation.%20Romy%20put%20together%20a%20ton%20of%20amazing%20inspiration%20images%2C%20and%20used%20a%20laser%20level%20to%20draw%20some%20stellar%20murals.%20It%20really%20is%20these%20murals%20that%20make%20the%20place%20pop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20were%20also%20able%20to%20source%20amazing%20vintage%20products%20on%20Facebook%20Marketplace%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20sourced%20vintage%20TVs%2C%20record%20players%2C%20and%20art.%20A%20big%20win%20came%20when%20a%20friend%20of%20ours%20was%20%26quot%3Bdecolorizing%26quot%3B%20her%20home%3B%20we%20scored%20a%20gorgeous%20EQ3%20couch%20that%20we%20never%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20afford%20otherwise%2C%20along%20with%20a%20handful%20of%20other%20items.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22756%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20living%20room%20area.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b047a2c22d1a0019455541%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22567%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJivan%20got%20this%20couch%20from%20a%20friend.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Qaid%20Jivan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%20though%2C%20my%20favorite%20pieces%20are%20the%20framed%20Vancouver%20Sun%20articles%20from%201969%20that%20hang%20in%20our%20living%20room.%20Although%20this%20style%20is%20very%20labor-intensive%2C%20it%20was%20cost-effective%20and%20absolutely%20worth%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20was%20a%20challenge%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20to%20price%20the%20AirBnB%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-host-shares-top-software-tools-to-run-efficient-business-2023-6%5C%22%3Efirst-time%20AirBnB%20hosts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20to%20charge.%20When%20we%20first%20started%2C%20we%20used%20the%20platform's%20automatic%20pricing%20feature%2C%20which%20uses%20its%20internal%20algorithm%20to%20determine%20a%20recommended%20price.%20We%20decided%20to%20charge%20about%20%24140%20a%20night%20during%20the%20off-season%20and%20upwards%20of%20%24180%20a%20night%C2%A0%20during%20the%20summer%20and%20holidays.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20could%20charge%20more%20since%20there%20aren't%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20two-bedroom%20apartments%20available%20in%20the%20area%20on%20AirBnB%2C%20but%20figuring%20out%20a%20sweet%20spot%20with%20pricing%20matters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20looking%20into%20other%20dynamic%20pricing%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe're%20averaging%20around%20%244%2C300%20in%20income%20a%20month%20from%20the%20AirBnB%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20real%20estate%20investment%20has%20already%20been%20profitable%20for%20us.%20To%20save%20money%2C%20we're%20strategic%20about%20how%20we%20use%20the%20%2450%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-airbnb-cleaning-fee-less-bookings-not-dipping-into-profit-2023-5%5C%22%3Ecleaning%20fee%20that%20our%20guests%20pay.%3C%2Fa%3E%20We%20usually%20hire%20my%20sister-in-law%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20cleaning%2C%20and%20when%20she%20can't%20do%20it%2C%20Alyssa%20or%20myself%20take%20over.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20operational%20expenses%20include%20a%20welcome%20basket%20that%20we%20give%20each%20guest.%20We%20spend%20around%20%2411%20on%20each%20basket%20and%20include%20a%20full-size%20Hardbite%20Chips%2C%20Lindt%20chocolate%2C%20and%20a%20bottle%20of%20San%20Pellegrino.%20Plus%2C%20we%20spend%20around%20%2416%20a%20guest%20on%20consumable%20products%20like%20soaps%2C%20shampoos%2C%20toilet%20paper%2C%20coffee%2C%20and%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222664%5C%22%2