%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fandrew-tate-sues-woman-who-accused-him-of-human-trafficking-12920813%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fandrew-tate-sues-woman-who-accused-him-of-human-trafficking-12920813%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google%20Stole%20%5C%22Everything%20Ever%20Created%20On%20Internet%5C%22%20To%20Train%20AI%20Chatbot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGoogle%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20lawsuit%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20accused%20the%20tech%20giant%20of%20%26quot%3Bsecretly%20stealing%20everything%20ever%20created%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20internet%26quot%3B%20in%20order%20to%20train%20its%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%20chatbot%20Bard.%20The%20complaint%2C%20filed%20in%20San%20Francisco%20federal%20court%20by%20eight%20individuals%20seeking%20to%20represent%20millions%20of%20internet%20users%20and%20copyright%20holders%2C%20said%20Google's%20unauthorised%20scraping%20of%20data%20from%20websites%20violated%20their%20privacy%20and%20property%20rights%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Ftech%2Fgoogle-bard-lawsuit-privacy-b2374719.html%5C%22%3Ereport%20in%20%3Cem%3EIndependent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20suit%20covers%20Google%2C%20its%20parent%20company%20Alphabet%20and%20Google's%20AI%20subsidiary%20DeepMind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPersonal%20data%20of%20every%20kind%2C%20especially%20conversational%20data%20between%20humans%2C%20is%20critical%20to%20the%20AI%20training%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftmsnrt.rs%2F3pGyDRz%5C%22%3Ethe%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20also%20claims%20that%20Google%20has%20even%20taken%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20and%20copywritten%20works%26quot%3B%20to%20build%20its%20AI%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20does%20not%20own%20the%20internet%2C%20it%20does%20not%20own%20our%20creative%20works%2C%20it%20does%20not%20own%20our%20expressions%20of%20our%20personhood%2C%20pictures%20of%20our%20families%20and%20children%2C%20or%20anything%20else%20simply%20because%20we%20share%20it%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20plaintiffs'%20attorney%20Ryan%20Clarkson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Google's%20general%20counsel%20Halimah%20DeLaine%20Prado%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20news%20agency%20Reuters%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bclear%20for%20years%20that%20we%20use%20data%20from%20public%20sources%20-%20like%20information%20published%20to%20the%20open%20web%20and%20public%20datasets%20-%20to%20train%20the%20AI%20models%20behind%20services%20like%20Google%20Translate%2C%20responsibly%20and%20in%20line%20with%20our%20AI%20principles%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmerican%20law%20supports%20using%20public%20information%20to%20create%20new%20beneficial%20uses%2C%20and%20we%20look%20forward%20to%20refuting%20these%20baseless%20claims%2C%26quot%3B%20DeLaine%20Prado%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20updated%20its%20online%20privacy%20policy%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20can%20use%20publicly%20available%20data%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lawsuit%20alleged%20that%20the%20change%20was%20designed%20to%20%26quot%3Bdouble-down%20on%20its%20position%20that%20everything%20on%20the%20internet%20is%20fair%20game%20for%20the%20company%20to%20take%20for%20private%20gain%20and%20commercial%20use%2C%20including%20to%20build%20and%20enhance%20AI%20products%20like%20Bard%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20one%20of%20several%20filed%20since%20last%20year%20against%20companies%20in%20the%20booming%20AI%20industry%2C%20including%20Meta%20Platforms%2C%20Microsoft%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20over%20their%20alleged%20misuse%20of%20personal%20data%20and%20copyrighted%20books%2C%20visual%20art%20and%20source%20code%20to%20train%20their%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%2