%20soon%20associated%20with%20Prighozin%2C%20but%20the%20business%20owner%20denied%20his%20involvement.%20Only%20in%20February%20this%20year%20did%20he%20admit%20to%20having%20founded%20the%20enterprise%20%E2%80%9Cto%20protect%20the%20Russian%20information%20space.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yevgeny%20Zubarev%2C%20head%20of%20Patriot%20Media%E2%80%99s%20largest%20resource%2C%20the%20Federal%20News%20Agency%20(FAN)%2C%20the%20troll%20factory%20dates%20as%20far%20back%20as%202009.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20commentators%20worked%20against%20opposition%20figures%20such%20as%20Alexei%20Navalny%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20private%20%E2%80%9Conline%20army%E2%80%9D%C2%A0grew%20and%20began%20operating%20internationally%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Justice%20Department%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwho-are-the-russian-trolls-indicted-by-the-us%2Fa-42650768%5C%22%3Eraised%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Russian%20firm%20for%20meddling%20in%20the%202016%20US%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETens%20of%20thousands%20of%20comments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20Prigozhin%20only%20had%20a%20few%20dozen%20workers%2C%20who%20had%20to%20write%20about%20100%20comments%20each%20per%20day.%20By%202023%2C%20the%20troll%20factory%20had%20grown%20to%20about%20400%20employees%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20wrote%20articles%20for%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20media%2C%20and%20at%20least%20a%20quarter%20of%20which%20wrote%20comments%20for%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigative%20Dossier%20Center%20says%20it%20is%20technically%20possible%20to%20spread%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20posts%20per%20day.%20The%20centre%20was%20founded%20by%20Kremlin%20critic%20and%20former%20owner%20of%20Yukos%20Oil%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmikhail-khodorkovsky-dialogue-only-strengthens-putins-regime%2Fa-59100697%5C%22%3EMikhail%20Khodorkovsky%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20now%20lives%20in%20London.%20Its%20website%20is%20banned%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20documents%20were%20leaked%20from%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20circles%2C%20the%20Dossier%20Center%20was%20able%20to%20publish%20details%20about%20the%20troll%20factory%2C%20according%20to%20which%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20internet%20empire%20has%20a%20disposable%20budget%20of%20some%20100%20million%20rubles%20(%E2%82%AC1%20million%2C%20%241%2C1%20million)%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14121048%2F1024px-Vladimir_Putin_and_Sergey_Shoigu_-_Saint-Petersburg_2017-07-30_1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14121048%2F1024px-Vladimir_Putin_and_Sergey_Shoigu_-_Saint-Petersburg_2017-07-30_1.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14121048%2F1024px-Vladimir_Putin_and_Sergey_Shoigu_-_Saint-Petersburg_2017-07-30_1-300x185.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663114%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20speaks%20with%20defence%20Minister%20Sergei%20Shoigu%20as%20they%20attend%20the%20Navy%20Day%20parade%20in%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20Russia%2C%20July%2030%2C%202017.%20Photo%3A%20Kremlin.ru%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20controls%20the%20media%20empire%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2024%2C%20while%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20advanced%20on%20Moscow%2C%20security%20forces%20searched%20the%20Lakhta%20business%20centre%20in%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20where%20employees%20of%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20media%20house%20kept%20their%20offices.%20Some%20of%20their%20websites%20have%20not%20been%20updated%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Twitter%20accounts%20RussiaActually%20and%20WorldActually%20only%20posted%20two%20tweets%20after%20June%2023%2C%20and%20have%20fallen%20completely%20silent%20since%20June%2029.%20Previously%2C%20they%20were%20known%20for%20releasing%20about%2010%20to%2012%20tweets%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20independent%20Russian%20website%20The%20Bell%20has%20reported%20that%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20online%20factory%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20owner.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.thebell.io%2Frussia-takes-direct-control-of-top-social-media-networks%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20According%20to%20The%20Bell%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bell%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20National%20Media%20Group%20owned%20by%20Yuri%20Kovalchuk%20is%20set%20to%20assume%20control%20over%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20media.%20The%20media%20group%20is%20chaired%20by%20former%20gymnast%20Alina%20Kabaeva%2C%20rumoured%20to%20be%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20girlfriend.%20Billionaire%20Kovalchuk%20is%20considered%20a%20close%20friend%20of%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20later%20informed%20The%20Bell%20that%20Prigozhin%20himself%20had%20decided%20to%20shutter%20his%20media%20empire.%20It%20reported%C2%A0that%20he%20had%20instructed%20his%20editors%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.thebell.io%2Fprigozhin-abandons-media-empire-following-failed-mutiny%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Beliminate%20everything%26quot%3B%20and%20remove%20%26quot%3Ball%20traces%20of%20an%20online%20presence%2C%26quot%3B%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Celiminate%20everything%E2%80%9D%20and%20remove%20%E2%80%9Call%20traces%20of%20an%20online%20presence%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0including%20websites%20and%20any%20associated%20social%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Roskomnadzor%2C%20the%20Russian%20federal%20agency%20for%20monitoring%20and%20controlling%20Russian%20media%2C%20had%20limited%20access%20to%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20media%2C%20including%20to%20FAN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20the%20online%20trolls%20done%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%20sees%20no%20reason%20to%20celebrate%20a%20victory%20over%20fake%20news%20and%20internet%20trolls.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20too%20early%20to%20make%20any%20definitive%20judgments%20about%20the%20developments%20in%20the%20Russian%20disinformation%20ecosystem%20after%20the%20alleged%20shutting%20down%20of%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20disinformation%C2%A0activities%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Peter%20Stano%2C%20EU%20Spokesperson%20for%20Foreign%20Affairs%20and%20Security%20Policy%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20who%20have%20been%20observing%20trolls%20for%20a%20long%20time%20time%2C%20also%20doubt%20that%20things%20are%20over.%20The%20Twitter%20user%20Bot%20Blocker%2C%20who%20operates%20with%20the%20handle%20%40antibot4navalny%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20were%20other%20social%20media%20commentators%20active%20outside%20of%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20media%20projects.%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20work%20has%20not%20let%20off%20much%20since%20the%20mutiny%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0the%20user%2C%20who%20wished%20to%20remain%20anonymous%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPro-Kremlin%20trolls%20or%20bots%20are%20still%20active%20and%20are%20even%20creating%20new%20Twitter%20accounts%20%E2%80%A6%20In%20the%20past%20few%20days%2C%20we%20have%20not%20observed%20any%20significant%20interruption%20or%20impairment%20of%20their%20operations%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20user%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20creators%20of%20the%20project%20%E2%80%9CChef%E2%80%99s%20Trap%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0who%20track%20internet%20troll%20on%20the%20Russian%20social%20networking%20service%C2%A0%3Cem%3EVKontakte%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20agreed.%20%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20of%20media%20outlets%20are%20writing%20that%20the%20well-known%20troll%20factory%20closed%20on%20June%2024%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0the%20project%E2%80%99s%20website%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20name%20is%20a%20play%20on%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20occasional%20nickname%20as%20%E2%80%9CPutin%E2%80%99s%20Chef%2C%E2%80%9D%20referring%20to%20the%20fortunes%20he%20amassed%20thanks%20to%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20patronage%20of%20his%20catering%20company%20Concord.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20leads%20the%20trolls%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20whom%20do%20these%20trolls%20follow%3F%20Observers%20are%20unsure.%20The%20Chef%E2%80%99s%20Trap%20project%20writes%20that%2C%20since%20May%2C%20when%20the%20conflict%20between%20Prigozhin%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20began%20escalating%2C%20most%20trolls%20have%20been%20writing%20posts%20critical%20of%20Prigozhin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20some%2013%2C000%20of%20an%20estimated%2015%2C000%20trolls%20in%20total%20have%20stopped%20supporting%20their%20mutinous%20boss.%20At%20Chef%E2%80%99s%20Trap%2C%20it%20is%20believed%20that%20Prigozhin%20has%20had%20his%20troll%20factory%20taken%20away%20from%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20user%20Bot%20Blocker%20believes%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20trolls%E2%80%99%20behaviour%20and%20rhetoric%20continue%20to%20follow%20the%20Kremlin%E2%80%99s%20interests%2C%20the%20same%20as%20during%20our%20entire%20observation%20period.%20The%20changed%20%E2%80%98attitude%E2%80%99%20towards%20Prigozhin%20probably%20indicates%20the%20changed%20reporting%20on%20him%20in%20the%20news%2C%20and%20not%20the%20handing%20over%20of%20the%20factory%20to%20some%20other%20nominal%20%E2%80%98owner.'%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%20does%20not%20expect%20Russian%20disinformation%20to%20dissipate%2C%20e