hing%20he%20wrote%2C%20he%20opened%20up%20new%20ways%20of%20thinking%2C%20reading%20and%20writing.%20In%20his%20literary%20presence%2C%20the%20world%20seemed%20tuned%20to%20a%20higher%20frequency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKundera%20was%20born%20with%20immaculate%20timing%2C%20on%20April%201%2C%201929%20(April%20Fool%E2%80%99s%20Day).%20From%20the%20start%2C%20he%20was%20exposed%C2%A0%20immersed%20in%2C%20the%20absurdity%20of%20human%20culture.%20He%20grew%20up%20in%20Nazi-occupied%20Czechoslovakia%2C%20then%20lived%20under%20Stalinist%20rule%2C%20where%20he%20was%20an%20active%20member%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20reading%20him%2C%20quoting%20him%20and%20teaching%20from%20his%20writings%20for%20decades%2C%20after%20bumping%20into%20his%20work%20in%201988.%20I%20was%20living%2C%20then%2C%20on%20an%20isolated%20sheep%20station%20in%20the%20Western%20Australian%20outback%2C%20a%20world%20of%20bleak%20beauty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20visiting%20the%20property%20pressed%20on%20me%20a%20copy%20of%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fliterariness.org%2F2022%2F10%2F09%2Fanalysis-of-milan-kunderas-the-book-of-laughter-and-forgetting%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Book%20of%20Laughter%20and%20Forgetting%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20I%20was%20immediately%20and%20utterly%20captivated.%20This%2C%20Kundera%E2%80%99s%20third%20novel%2C%20affirmed%20my%20own%20anxiety%20of%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20stable%20truth%2C%20and%20of%20my%20incapacity%20to%20resist%20the%20longing%20to%20belong%2C%20even%20to%20the%20most%20damaged%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20section%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20a%20group%20of%20the%20Communist%20faithful%2C%20dancing%20together%20in%20a%20circle%2C%20rise%20into%20the%20air%20and%20soar%20over%20the%20city.%20They%20laugh%20the%20laughter%20of%20angels%20while%20below%20them%2C%20the%20executioners%20are%20killing%20political%20prisoners.%20Says%20the%20narrator%20of%20this%20section%2C%20who%20necessarily%20cannot%20be%20part%20of%20that%20group%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20realized%20with%20anguish%20in%20my%20heart%20that%20they%20were%20flying%20like%20birds%20and%20I%20was%20falling%20like%20a%20stone%2C%20that%20they%20had%20wings%20and%20I%20would%20never%20have%20any.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterrogating%20totalitarianism%2C%20with%20humour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKundera%20knew%20about%20oppression%20and%20inhumanity.%20His%20first%20collection%20of%20(not%20very%20good)%20poetry%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMan%2C%20A%20Wide%20Garden%20(1953)%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20was%20published%20when%20he%20was%20only%2024%20%E2%80%93%20was%20decidedly%20Soviet%20in%20tone%20and%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20he%20wrote%20his%20first%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera%2C-translated-by-Michael-Henry-Heim-Joke-9780571166930%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Joke%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%201967%2C%20then%20wrote%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera%2C-translated-by-Aaron-Asher-Life-is-Elsewhere-9780571197774%2F%5C%22%3ELife%20is%20Elsewhere%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201969%20(published%20in%201973)%2C%20both%20of%20them%20shot%20through%20with%20political%20satire%2C%20and%20he%20was%20expelled%20from%20the%20Communist%20Party%20and%20subsequently%20fled%20into%20exile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20is%20perhaps%20his%20best-known%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera%2C-translated-by-Michael-Henry-Heim-Unbearable-Lightness-of-Being-9780571135394%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Unbearable%20Lightness%20of%20Being%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1984)%20%E2%80%93%20adapted%20in%201988%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0096332%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20movie%3C%2Fa%3E%20starring%20Daniel%20Day-Lewis%20and%20Juliette%20Binoche%20%E2%80%93%20he%20continues%20his%20interrogation%20of%20totalitarian%20politics%2C%20exploring%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FPrague-Spring%5C%22%3EPrague%20Spring%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20brutality%20of%20Soviet%20control%20of%20Czechoslavakia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20theme%20sounds%20deeply%20earnest.%20But%20in%20each%20novel%2C%20Kundera%20offers%20some%20humour%20%E2%80%93%20often%20bitter%2C%20but%20capable%20of%20leavening%20the%20otherwise%20bleak%2C%20and%20densely%20reported%2C%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EUnbearable%20Lightness%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20example%2C%20the%20narrator%20discusses%20Nietszche%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphilosophybreak.com%2Farticles%2Feternal-recurrence-what-did-nietzsche-really-mean%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DLoeb%2520argues%2520that%2520in%2Cand%2520history%2520will%2520repeat%2520itself%5C%22%3Edoctrine%20of%20eternal%20recurrence%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20possibility%20we%20live%20the%20same%20life%20over%20and%20over.%20But%20he%20also%20develops%20an%20erotic%20narrative%20that%20seems%20to%20suggest%20lighthearted%20sex%20can%20allow%20us%20to%20live%20fully%20in%20the%20moment.%20We%20can%20exchange%20the%20weight%20of%20eternal%20recurrence%20for%20the%20lightness%20of%20being%20alive%2C%20here%20and%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeight%20and%20lightness%2C%20laughter%20and%20forgetting%2C%20repetition%20and%20change%2C%20politics%20and%20sex%3A%20his%20first%20four%20novels%20incorporate%20such%20dualities.%20Perhaps%20this%20capacity%20to%20hold%20contradictory%20thoughts%20can%20be%20explained%20by%20something%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kundera.de%2Fenglish%2FInfo-Point%2FInterview_Roth%2Finterview_roth.html%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Philip%20Roth%3A%20%E2%80%9CTotalitarianism%20is%20not%20only%20hell%2C%20but%20also%20the%20dream%20of%20paradise%20%E2%80%93%20the%20age%20old%20drama%20of%20a%20world%20where%20everybody%20would%20live%20in%20harmony.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FpG2Gsoet7p0%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%20in%20exile%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20dream%20of%20paradise%20was%20not%20realised%2C%20of%20course.%20In%201975%2C%20he%20fled%20his%20home%20for%20exile%20in%20France%2C%20and%20continued%20writing%20works%20of%20fiction%20that%20mostly%20followed%20the%20signature%20structure%20he%20first%20developed%20in%20The%20Joke%3A%20multi-part%2C%20multi-voiced%20novels%2C%20where%20the%20narrator%20interpolates%20critique%2C%20commentary%20and%20philosophical%20statements%20in%20the%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20makes%20for%20a%20restless%20story%2C%20one%20that%20shifts%20to%20and%20fro%20across%20locations%2C%20times%20and%20contexts.%20Characters%20flicker%20in%20and%20out.%20The%20logic%20of%20beginning%2C%20middle%20and%20end%20is%20barely%20acknowledged.%20And%20the%20sorts%20of%20issues%20that%20appear%20so%20often%20in%20fiction%20%E2%80%93%20a%20quest%20for%20the%20self%2C%20the%20telling%20of%20a%20tale%2C%20the%20achievement%20of%20resolution%20%E2%80%93%20are%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20focus%20of%20Kundera%E2%80%99s%20novels%20is%20their%20wrestle%20with%20questions%20of%20knowledge%2C%20the%20complexity%20of%20being%20and%20a%20constant%20uncertainty.%20This%20can%20be%20an%20unsettling%20style%3A%20a%20disruption%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20simple%20pleasure%20or%20an%20aesthetic%20experience.%20For%20a%2021st-century%20woman%2C%20too%2C%20his%20tone%20and%20style%20in%20the%20writing%20of%20sex%20scenes%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20more%20generally%20%E2%80%93%20can%20present%20as%20outdated%20masculinity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20vacillate%20between%20feeling%20offence%20at%20what%20feels%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcultural-misogyny-and-why-mens-aggression-to-women-is-so-often-expressed-through-sex-157680%5C%22%3Emisogyny%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20reading%20it%20as%20a%20searing%20critique%20of%20misogyny.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2015%2Fmay%2F22%2Fmilan-kundera-immortality-jonathan-coe-novels-women%5C%22%3EI%E2%80%99m%20not%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Things%20are%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20you%20think%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhere%20I%20uncomplicatedly%20follow%20Kundera%E2%80%99s%20lead%20is%20not%20in%20his%20novels%2C%20but%20in%20his%20essays.%20Here%2C%20his%20deep%20understanding%20of%20the%20background%20to%20what%20we%20now%20know%20as%20the%20novel%2C%20or%20the%20long%20traditions%20and%20changes%20that%20characterise%20artistic%20practice%2C%20genuinely%20illuminate%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Art-of-the-Novel-9780571227495%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Art%20of%20the%20Novel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1986)%2C%20he%20outlines%20a%20history%20of%20how%20novelists%20unpacked%20various%20dimensions%20of%20existence.%20He%20starts%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FMiguel_de_Cervantes%5C%22%3EMiguel%20de%20Cervantes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20moves%20through%20the%20lists%20of%20generative%20fiction%20writers%20to%20fellow%20Czechs%20Franz%20Kafka%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FJaroslav_Ha%25C5%25A1ek%5C%22%3EJaroslav%20Hasek%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20who%2C%20he%20claims%2C%20show%20that%20a%20strength%20of%20fiction%20is%20that%20it%20tolerates%20uncertainty%2C%20in%20a%20way%20politics%20and%20religion%20cannot.%20For%20Kundera%2C%20what%20fiction%20does%20so%20well%20is%20say%20to%20the%20reader%3A%20%E2%80%9CThings%20are%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20you%20think.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Kundera%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20a%20technological%20object%20that%20allows%20new%20ways%20of%20seeing%2C%20and%20of%20making%20meaning.%20And%20this%20seeing%20and%20meaning%20is%20embedded%20in%20its%20context.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2007%2F03%2F04%2Fbooks%2Freview%2FBanks.t.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Curtain%3A%20An%20Essay%20in%20Seven%20Parts%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2006)%2C%20he%20points%20out%20what%20fiction%20can%20do%20that%20earlier%20forms%20could%20not.%20Homer%20never%20wondered%20whether%2C%20after%20all%20their%20many%20hand-to-hand%20battles%2C%20Achilles%20or%20Ajax%20still%20had%20all%20their%20teeth.%20But%20for%20Don%20Quixote%20and%20Sancho%20teeth%20are%20a%20perpetual%20concern%20%E2%80%93%20hurting%20teeth%2C%20missing%20teeth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriters%20like%20Cervantes%20(author%20of%20Don%20Quixote)%2C%20Henry%20Fielding%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_History_of_Tom_Jones%2C_a_Foundling%5C%22%3ETom%20Jones%3C%2Fa%3E)%20and%20Laurence%20Sterne%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goodreads.com%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F76527.The_Life_and_Opinions_of_Tristram_Shandy_Gentleman%5C%22%3EThe%20Life%20and%20Opinions%20of%20Tristam%20Shandy%2C%20Gentleman%3C%2Fa%3E)%20introduce%20the%20small%20things%20of%20everyday%20life%2C%20and%20illuminate%20the%20meaning%20and%20import%20they%20have%20on%20us%2C%20Kundera%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20hastens%20to%20observe%2C%20contemporary%20writers%20cannot%20and%20should%20not%20write%20as%20those%20giants%20did%3A%20rather%2C%20writing%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20continuity%20(in%20terms%20of%20form%2C%20voice%20and%20style%20in%20a%20particular%20period)%20and%20discontinuity%20(finding%20something%20new).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20essays%2C%20too%2C%20he%20offers%20a%20workshop%20in%20how%20to%20write.%20How%20to%20manage%20voice%2C%20perspective%2C%20temporality.%20How%20to%20have%20fun%20with%20language%20and%20form%20%E2%80%93%20and%20let%20the%20imagination%20run%20wild.%20And%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20thought%20and%20concept%2C%20materiality%20and%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeller%20of%20inconvenient%20truths%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20writer%20of%20such%20gravitas%20and%20such%20technical%20brilliance%20should%2C%20one%20might%20imagine%2C%20have%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Literature%20at%20some%20point%20in%20his%20long%20life.%20He%20won%20other%20prizes%2C%20after%20all%2C%20among%20them%20the%20Jerusalem%20Prize%20in%201985%20and%20the%20Herder%20Prize%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20it%20was%20his%20writing%20style%20that%20meant%20the%20Nobel%20committee%20saw%20him%20nominated%20on%20a%20number%20of%20occasions%2C%20but%20never%20awarded%20him%20the%20prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20last%20novel%20he%20wrote%20in%20Czech%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera%2C-translated-by-Peter-Kussi-Immortality-9780571144563%2F%5C%22%3EImmortality%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1991)%2C%20which%20teases%20out%20questions%20of%20sexual%20and%20personal%20relationships%20%E2%80%93%20he%20wrote%20four%20more%20novels%2C%20which%20garnered%20less%20attention%2C%20less%20critical%20reception.%20So%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Slowness-9780571179435%2F%5C%22%3ESlowness%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1995)%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Identity-9780571195671%2F%5C%22%3EIdentity%3A%20A%20Novel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1999)%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Ignorance-9780571215515%2F%5C%22%3EIgnorance%3C%2Fa%3E%20(%3C%2Fem%3E2000)%20and%20finally%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Festival-of-Insignificance-9780571316496%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Festival%20of%20Insignificance%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2014)%2C%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F12%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fmilan-kundera-dead.html%5C%22%3Ecan%20see%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20star%20begin%20to%20fade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20because%20they%20are%20less%20%E2%80%9Cgood%E2%80%9D%20books.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fquillette.com%2F2023%2F07%2F11%2Fmilan-kundera-the-nobel-prize-for-literature-winner-we-never-had%2F%5C%22%3ERobin%20Ashenden%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20%E2%80%9Chad%20become%20a%20teller%20of%20truths%20inconvenient%20to%20the%20modern%20age%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20maybe%20there%20is%20something%20in%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20terribly%20direct%2C%20very%20hard-hitting.%20And%20he%20refuses%20the%20consolations%20of%20sentimentality%20or%20morality%2C%20in%20favour%20of%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FMilan-Kundera-Art-of-the-Novel-9780571227495%2F%5C%22%3Ehe%20describes%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20morality%20of%20knowledge%3A%20the%20imperative%20to%20see%20and%20say%20what%20previous%20writers%20did%20not%2Fcould%20not%20see%2C%20or%20say.%20And%20to%20build%20fresh%20understandings%20of%20the%20world.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F209679%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fjen-webb-115178%5C%22%3EJen%20Webb%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dean%2C%20Graduate%20Research%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-canberra-865%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Canberra